    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but what's the point of that \"intensity\" though? it's just more suffering to fuel it. if you know for a fact that everything you are and everything you feel is eventually going to be annihilated by entropy, isn't it just... illogical to keep going? it feels like we're just being forced to run a race that has no finish line, just a cliff at the end. why is it considered \"good\" to keep struggling through the pain when there's no actual payoff? it just feels like a waste of energy.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
